reviews_data.review_text: Great 👍🏽

**Incredible Coffee Experience!**
My husband and I visit every Sunday, and it's always a delight. I usually get a peppermint iced coffee, while he enjoys a classic black coffee. Their tiramisu is simply delicious! We were pleasantly surprised at how affordable our coffee was, and we even ended up purchasing coffee beans to enjoy at home. Highly recommend!
Great coffee and friendly service

Stopped by for a coffee and croissant. Coffee is good, croissant is stale. Gave it back to be discarded and told the owner it was inedible. He asked if I wanted a fresh one. Unbelievable. Won't be back.

I think their food is a very and good quality!!
The Greek salad David fixed for me was excellent!
Quality food and customer service! Everything on the menu tastes amazing!!
Found this little place by accident and so glad I did.  The service was quick and friendly. The coffee was flavorful and the croissants were delightfully light and buttery.  I will be back!!
A great cup of coffee, food looked delicious, bright atmosphere. Can’t wait to go back. Our new coffee spot in Waxhaw for sure.
Had a great cup of coffee and learned about the Jebena ceremony. A welcoming place for friends and others.

I just had the most delightful experience at Jebena Cafe in Waxhaw! I'd been wanting to try it for a while, and let me tell you, it did not disappoint.

The atmosphere is warm and inviting. It's not a huge place, but it has a cozy vibe that makes you feel right at home. I went for a lunchtime visit, and there were a few people catching up with friends over steaming cups of coffee, while others were focused on laptops.

Speaking of coffee, that's definitely the star of the show here. I opted for a traditional Ethiopian brew, and it was unlike any coffee I'd ever had before. Rich, complex, and aromatic – it was a true flavor explosion. They even have the whole brewing ceremony on display, which was fascinating to watch.

For food, I went with the chicken salad croissant. It sounds simple, but the flavors were fantastic. The chicken salad was perfectly seasoned and packed with fresh ingredients, and the croissant itself was buttery and flaky. The portions were generous, and I left feeling happy and satisfied.

The staff at Jebena Cafe were friendly and helpful. They were happy to answer my questions about the menu and the coffee brewing process.  Overall, it was a fantastic experience, and I can't wait to go back and try some of their other offerings.  If you're looking for a unique and delicious coffee experience in Waxhaw, Jebena Cafe is definitely worth checking out!

For food, I went with the chicken salad croissant. It sounds simple, but the flavors were fantastic. The chicken salad was perfectly seasoned and packed with fresh ingredients, and the croissant itself was buttery and flaky. The portions were generous, and I left feeling happy and satisfied.

The staff at Jebena Cafe were friendly and helpful. They were happy to answer my questions about the menu and the coffee brewing process.  Overall, it was a fantastic experience, and I can't wait to go back and try some of their other offerings.  If you're looking for a unique and delicious coffee experience in Waxhaw, Jebena Cafe is definitely worth checking out!
